To make a list collapsible by clicking only on the header of the list, you can use the CSS `display` property. Here is an example of how you can do this:
HTML:
```
html<ul>
  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
  <li>Item 3</li>
</ul>
```
CSS:
```
ul {
  list-style: none;
}
li {
  display: none;
}
li:first-child {
  display: block;
}
li:hover + li {
  display: block;
}
li:hover {
  cursor: pointer;
}
```
This will make the list collapsible by clicking only on the header of the list.

